CVE-2024-38819: Path traversal fix for double-encoded static resource paths

This patch addresses a follow-on path traversal vulnerability in Spring
Framework's functional web frameworks (WebMvc.fn and WebFlux.fn) and static
resource handlers. It adds normalizePath/decode handling for double URL
encoding and tightens "../" detection after path normalization.

Must be applied after CVE-2024-38816.

Origin: upstream, https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/commit/fb7890d73975a3d9e0763e0926df2bd0a608e87e
Bug: CVE-2024-38819

